### ============================================================================
### Test File: Connection Invitations Email System
### Usage: Use REST Client extension in VSCode
### ============================================================================

### Variables
@supabaseUrl = https://uzywajqzbdbrfammshdg.supabase.co
@anonKey = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InV6eXdhanF6YmRicmZhbW1zaGRnIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3MzMwODY1ODksImV4cCI6MjA0ODY2MjU4OX0.U4VePSYyCq0UkETOPH0SwR-Ay1VbmKNV1yPE9JxJxio
@accessToken = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================================================
### 1. Test Edge Function Directly (Manual Test)
### ============================================================================

POST {{supabaseUrl}}/functions/v1/send-invitation-email
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "invitation_id": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000",
  "to_email": "test@example.com",
  "inviter_name": "João Silva",
  "space_name": "Família Silva",
  "space_archetype": "habitat",
  "token": "abc123def456ghi789jkl012mno345pq"
}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "success": true,
###   "message": "Invitation email sent successfully",
###   "messageId": "resend-message-id-123"
### }


### ============================================================================
### 2. Create Invitation (Via Database RPC - For Testing)
### ============================================================================

POST {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_invitations
Content-Type: application/json
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Prefer: return=representation

{
  "space_id": "YOUR_SPACE_ID_HERE",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "token": "abc123def456ghi789jkl012mno345pq",
  "status": "pending",
  "invited_by": "YOUR_USER_ID_HERE",
  "role": "member",
  "expires_at": "2026-02-05T23:59:59Z",
  "email_delivery_status": "pending"
}

### Expected Response: Created invitation object


### ============================================================================
### 3. Query Invitations (Check Status)
### ============================================================================

GET {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_invitations?select=*&order=created_at.desc&limit=10
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expected Response: Array of invitations


### ============================================================================
### 4. Query Invitation by Email
### ============================================================================

GET {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_invitations?select=*&email=eq.test@example.com
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expected Response: Invitations for specific email


### ============================================================================
### 5. Query Invitation by Token
### ============================================================================

GET {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_invitations?select=*&token=eq.abc123def456ghi789jkl012mno345pq
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expected Response: Single invitation object


### ============================================================================
### 6. Update Email Status (Simulate Email Sent)
### ============================================================================

PATCH {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_invitations?id=eq.YOUR_INVITATION_ID
Content-Type: application/json
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Prefer: return=representation

{
  "email_sent_at": "2026-01-29T12:00:00Z",
  "email_delivery_status": "sent"
}

### Expected Response: Updated invitation object


### ============================================================================
### 7. Test Resend API Directly (Bypass Edge Function)
### ============================================================================

POST https://api.resend.com/emails
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_RESEND_API_KEY

{
  "from": "noreply@resend.dev",
  "to": "test@example.com",
  "subject": "Test Email from Aica",
  "html": "<h1>Hello from Aica!</h1><p>This is a test email.</p>"
}

### Expected Response:
### {
###   "id": "resend-message-id"
### }


### ============================================================================
### 8. Query Space Details (For Testing)
### ============================================================================

GET {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_spaces?select=id,name,archetype,user_id&limit=5
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expected Response: Array of connection spaces


### ============================================================================
### 9. Query Connection Members (Verify Permissions)
### ============================================================================

GET {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_members?select=*&space_id=eq.YOUR_SPACE_ID
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Expected Response: Array of members


### ============================================================================
### 10. Test Security: Try to Create Invitation for Another User's Space
### ============================================================================

POST {{supabaseUrl}}/rest/v1/connection_invitations
Content-Type: application/json
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Prefer: return=representation

{
  "space_id": "ANOTHER_USER_SPACE_ID",
  "email": "malicious@example.com",
  "token": "malicioustoken123",
  "status": "pending",
  "invited_by": "YOUR_USER_ID",
  "role": "admin",
  "expires_at": "2026-02-05T23:59:59Z"
}

### Expected Response: 403 Forbidden (RLS policy blocks)


### ============================================================================
### Notes:
### - Replace YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE with real JWT from Supabase Auth
### - Replace YOUR_SPACE_ID_HERE with actual space ID
### - Replace YOUR_USER_ID_HERE with your authenticated user ID
### - Replace YOUR_RESEND_API_KEY with Resend API key
### - Use REST Client extension in VSCode to run these requests
### ============================================================================
